        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): deliver reasoning as durable block when /reasoning on",
        "body": "## Summary\nFix `/reasoning on` dropping the thinking lane on Telegram. When reasoning mode is \"on\" (not \"stream\"), the `onReasoningStream` callback was unconditionally `undefined` because both the reasoning draft stream and the progress draft path were inactive. This caused the model's thinking content to be silently lost — produced and archived, but never delivered to the Telegram chat.\n\nThe fix adds a third fallback branch that sends reasoning text as a durable (non-streaming) block message when `forceBlockStreamingForReasoning` is true. It also wires `onReasoningEnd` for the block-streaming path to reset progress state.\n\nFixes #94937\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n**Behavior addressed**: Under `/reasoning on`, the model's `<think>` content is generated and archived but never rendered on Telegram. Under `/reasoning stream` the same content streams in an ephemeral block correctly.\n\n**Real setup tested**:\n- **Runtime**: Node 24.13.1, Linux x64\n- **Code analysis path**: See root cause analysis in issue comments (5 Whys)\n- **Test framework**: Vitest\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.test.ts --run\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n```\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  130 passed (130)\n   Start at  22:19:21\n   Duration  19.52s\n```\n\n**Observed result after the fix**: `onReasoningStream` callback is now defined when `/reasoning on` is active. The extracted and formatted reasoning text (e.g. `Thinking\\n\\n_ambient reasoning_`) is delivered via durable `sendPayload` instead of being silently dropped. No reasoning draft stream is created in \"on\" mode, matching intent.\n\n**What was not tested**: Live Telegram end-to-end test with real model thinking output (requires configured bot + reasoning-capable model). The fix was verified at unit-test level and by tracing the full callback chain from `onReasoningStream` → `splitTelegramReasoningText` → `sendPayload` → `deliverInboundReplyWithMessageSendContext`.\n\n## Tests and validation\n| Test Type | Result | Details |\n|-----------|--------|---------|\n| Unit Tests | ✅ | 130 passed, includes new test for reasoning \"on\" durable delivery |\n| Type Check | N/A | `tsgo` lanes only — not run locally per repo policy |\n| Lint | N/A | `oxfmt`/`oxlint` config on file — no structural issues detected |\n\n## Risk checklist\n**Did user-visible behavior change?** `Yes` — `/reasoning on` now delivers thinking as persistent block messages on Telegram (previously silent drop).\n**Did config, environment, or migration behavior change?** `No`\n**Did security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change?** `No`\n\n## Current review state\n**What is the next action?** Maintainer review requested\n",
